# Hubly brand logo

The official Hubly logo is the lowercase wordmark **hub** + **ly**:

- **hub** — dark navy (`#141B2B`) on light UI · **white** on dark UI
- **ly** — bright orange (`#D9632D`)
- Font feel: clean, modern, bold sans (Plus Jakarta Sans / DM Sans weight 700–800)
- **No background box. No underline / bar under the wordmark.** Transparent PNG/SVG only.

## Asset files

- Light backgrounds: `assets/hubly-wordmark.png` (also `public/assets/…`, SVG twin available)
- Dark backgrounds: `assets/hubly-wordmark-on-dark.png` (white hub + orange ly)

## Rules

1. Whenever Hubly appears as a **logo / brand mark** (nav, hero, auth, boot, footer, coach chrome, empty states), use the official wordmark treatment — **not** plain unstyled text "Hubly" / "HubLy".
2. Preferred mark: CSS text wordmark matching Instant Site (`hub` + `<span>ly</span>`) — white/navy hub, **ly always brand orange `#D9632D`** (same as accent CTAs / “help”), **no background plate, no underline**. Do not use soft gold (`#fdba74`) for the mark. Image assets (`hubly-wordmark*.png` / `.svg`) must match that orange.
3. In body copy (“Hubly builds…”, “Hubly Coach”), capitalized Hubly is fine as text; when the coach header or FAB branding shows, still use the mark.
4. Do not invent a different logo treatment (all-orange, emoji, icon-only, title case HubLy, underlines, white/navy plates behind the mark, etc.).
5. Brand accent CTAs should stay in the logo orange family (`#D9632D` / `--brand`).
